 {"id":"bd-3mi","title":"FilesystemProvider - Built-in filesystem resource provider","description":"# FilesystemProvider - Built-in Filesystem Resource Provider

## Background
Python FastMCP provides a built-in FilesystemProvider that allows servers to easily expose filesystem directories as MCP resources. This is a common use case - many MCP servers simply need to expose files from specific directories with appropriate access controls.

## Requirements

### Core API
```rust
/// Builder for filesystem resource provider
pub struct FilesystemProvider {
    root: PathBuf,
    prefix: Option<String>,
    include_patterns: Vec<String>,
    exclude_patterns: Vec<String>,
    recursive: bool,
    watch: bool,
    max_file_size: usize,
    follow_symlinks: bool,
}

impl FilesystemProvider {
    /// Create a new provider for the given root directory
    pub fn new(root: impl AsRef<Path>) -> Self

    /// Set the URI prefix (e.g., "docs" -> "file://docs/...")
    pub fn with_prefix(self, prefix: &str) -> Self

    /// Include only files matching these glob patterns
    pub fn with_patterns(self, patterns: &[&str]) -> Self

    /// Exclude files matching these glob patterns
    pub fn with_exclude(self, patterns: &[&str]) -> Self

    /// Enable recursive directory traversal
    pub fn with_recursive(self, enabled: bool) -> Self

    /// Enable filesystem watching for change notifications
    pub fn with_watch(self, enabled: bool) -> Self

    /// Set maximum file size to serve (bytes)
    pub fn with_max_size(self, bytes: usize) -> Self

    /// Control symlink behavior
    pub fn with_follow_symlinks(self, enabled: bool) -> Self

    /// Build and register with server
    pub fn build(self) -> impl ResourceProvider
}

// Usage
let provider = FilesystemProvider::new("/data/docs")
    .with_prefix("docs")
    .with_patterns(&["**/*.md", "**/*.txt"])
    .with_exclude(&["**/secret/**", "**/.*"])
    .with_recursive(true)
    .with_max_size(10 * 1024 * 1024) // 10MB
    .build();

server.add_resource_provider(provider);
```

### Resource URIs
- Individual file: `file://docs/readme.md`
- Directory listing: `file://docs/` (returns list of files)
- With prefix: `file://{prefix}/{relative_path}`
- Without prefix: `file://{relative_path}`

